          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Gemellus muscle laterally rotates the femur at the hip joint. Superior gemellus muscle: Attaches proximally at the ischial spine; distally, the muscle attaches on the greater trochanter of the femur. The nerve to the obturator internus and superior gemellus muscles (L5, S1, S2) innervates this muscle.Inferior gemellus muscle: Attaches proximally on the ischial spine; distally, the muscle attaches at the greater trochanter of the femur. The nerve to the inferior gemellus and quadratus femoris muscles (L4, L5, S1) innervates this muscle."
