          "explanation": "Ans. is 'b' i.e., 3-4 cm \"The cricopharyngeal sphincter is 2-3 cm, and the lower esophageal sphincter (LES) is 3-4 cm long\". - Textbook of GI Surgeryo Approximately 2 cm of the esophagus lie below the diaphragm in the abdomen (abdominal part of esophagus)o Within this portion of esophagus the abdominal part of LES is locatedo Another 1-2 cm of LES lie above the diaphragm in mediastinum, i.e. thoracic part of LES.o Thus total length of LES is 3-4 cm.",
