          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Clearance is variable in zero-order kinetics because a constant amount of the drug is eliminated per unit time, but it is constant in first-order kinetics, because the amount of drug eliminated per unit time changes with the concentration of drug in the blood Ref-KDT 6/e p32",
          "hint": "Topic: General anatomy"
