          "explanation": "Apical alveoli have low ventilation and perfusion per unit volume of the lung, whereas the basal alveoli have high ventilation and perfusion.\nVentilation-perfusion ratio and the PaO2 is maximum at the apex. PCO2 is maximum at the base."
