          "id": "medmcqa-94c2904d-2d6d-4d92-9ad9-a88415418efb",
          "text": "Aerial blood gas of a 5 year old child done at sea level gives the following results: pH 7.41, PaO2, 100 mmHg, and PaCO2, 40 mmHg. The child is being ventilated with 80% oxygen. What is the (A-a) DO2.-",
